Thus he takes Guenon's supposed silence on Japan as a sign of idiosyncrasy. But some friends here have suggested that a lot of supposedly authentic Japanese traditions were fabricated post-contact with Europeans for purposes of legitimization. Maybe here lies an enigma of sorts.
